The paper introduces a novel approach for fast sensory evaluation using geometric techniques, which involves the use of a software to implement the proposed techniques. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the Human-Computer Interaction (cs.HC) sub-category. Additionally, the paper involves the use of clustering and graph drawing algorithms, which are commonly used in Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) and Machine Learning (cs.LG). The paper also mentions the comparison of pictures by a huge number of consumers via the Internet, which suggests that it may be related to Computer Vision (cs.CV) and Information Retrieval (cs.IR).
